properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 16 at 8:56PM CST until February 17 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...SNOW AND A WINTRY MIX DEVELOPING MONDAY...

* WHAT...Snow developing later Monday morning, with a rain and
snow mix expected Monday afternoon into the evening. Total snow
accumulations of 3 to 5 inches.

* WHERE...Marquette, Green Lake, Sauk and Columbia Counties.

* WHEN...From 9 AM to 9 PM CST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on deteriorating road conditions on Monday with
reduced visibility in falling snow. The hazardous conditions
will likely impact the afternoon and evening commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The snow will likely be wet and heavy, and
will be difficult to shovel. Plan to allow extra time to shovel
your drive and walk.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM TO 9 PM CST MONDAY
